-= Kitchen =-

You can see an opened fridge. The fridge contains a yellow bell pepper, a carrot and a white onion. Look over there! an oven. You can make out a table. You see a knife on the table. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see a counter. On the counter you make out a red hot pepper and a cookbook. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?

You are hungry! Let's cook a delicious meal. Check the cookbook in the kitchen for the recipe. Once done, enjoy your meal!

-= Kitchen =-
You find yourself in a kitchen. A standard one. You begin to take stock of what's in the room.

You can see an opened fridge. The fridge contains a yellow bell pepper, a carrot and a white onion. Look over there! an oven. You can make out a table. You see a knife on the table. As if things weren't amazing enough already, you can even see a counter. On the counter you make out a red hot pepper and a cookbook. You make out a stove. What a coincidence, weren't you just thinking about a stove? The stove is conventional. Unfortunately, there isn't a thing on it. What, you think everything in TextWorld should have stuff on it?
